window.bookSummaryJSON = "In this seminal story of naval life during the Napoleonic wars, Frederick Marryat's young hero embarks upon a life at sea and finds it to be a rough school indeed. Simple's trials and triumphs, with his faithful mentor, Terence O'Brien, at his side, mirror Marryat's personal experiences. Among the exciting events depicted are the hand-to-hand combat of \"cutting-out\" missions, the devastating hurricane off St. Pierre, and a mutiny aboard the <i>Rattlesnake</i>. <p><i>Peter Simple</i> is a towering tale from the great age of sail, filled with keen wit, vivid characters, and thrilling adventure.</p>"; 
